{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":926,"text":"The first time I cried underwater"},{"time":3374,"text":"was in 2008,"},{"time":4941,"text":"the island of Curaçao,"},{"time":6542,"text":"way down in the southern Caribbean."},{"time":8848,"text":"It's beautiful there."},{"time":10524,"text":"I was studying these corals for my PhD,"},{"time":13474,"text":"and after days and days\nof diving on the same reef,"},{"time":15880,"text":"I had gotten to know them as individuals."},{"time":17933,"text":"I had made friends with coral colonies --"},{"time":20428,"text":"totally a normal thing to do."},{"time":23260,"text":"Then, Hurricane Omar smashed them apart\nand ripped off their skin,"},{"time":27980,"text":"leaving little bits of wounded tissue\nthat would have a hard time healing,"},{"time":32493,"text":"and big patches of dead skeleton\nthat would get overgrown by algae."},{"time":36381,"text":"When I saw this damage for the first time,"},{"time":38429,"text":"stretching all the way down the reef,"},{"time":40263,"text":"I sunk onto the sand in my scuba gear"},{"time":42144,"text":"and I cried."},{"time":43564,"text":"If a coral could die that fast,"},{"time":45945,"text":"how could a reef ever survive?"},{"time":48354,"text":"And why was I making it my job\nto try to fight for them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51852,"text":"I never heard another scientist\ntell that kind of story"},{"time":54908,"text":"until last year."},{"time":56803,"text":"A scientist in Guam wrote,"},{"time":58832,"text":"\"I cried right into my mask,\""},{"time":60403,"text":"seeing the damage on the reefs."},{"time":63649,"text":"Then a scientist in Australia wrote,"},{"time":65614,"text":"\"I showed my students\nthe results of our coral surveys,"},{"time":68635,"text":"and we wept.\""},{"time":70896,"text":"Crying about corals\nis having a moment, guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73568,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74726,"text":"And that's because reefs in the Pacific"},{"time":76694,"text":"are losing corals faster\nthan we've ever seen before."},{"time":79869,"text":"Because of climate change,"},{"time":81165,"text":"the water is so hot for so long\nin the summers,"},{"time":83998,"text":"that these animals\ncan't function normally."},{"time":86674,"text":"They're spitting out the colored algae\nthat lives in their skin,"},{"time":89726,"text":"and the clear bleached tissue\nthat's left usually starves to death"},{"time":94815,"text":"and then rots away."},{"time":97124,"text":"Then the skeletons are overgrown by algae."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99961,"text":"This is happening\nover an unbelievable scale."},{"time":102308,"text":"The Northern Great Barrier Reef\nlost two-thirds of its corals last year"},{"time":106468,"text":"over a distance of hundreds of miles,"},{"time":109047,"text":"then bleached again this year,"},{"time":110873,"text":"and the bleaching stretched further south."},{"time":114004,"text":"Reefs in the Pacific\nare in a nosedive right now,"},{"time":116342,"text":"and no one knows\nhow bad it's going to get,"},{"time":118905,"text":"except ..."},{"time":120298,"text":"over in the Caribbean where I work,"},{"time":122261,"text":"we've already been through the nosedive."},{"time":124699,"text":"Reefs there have suffered\nthrough centuries of intense human abuse."},{"time":128944,"text":"We kind of already know\nhow the story goes."},{"time":131463,"text":"And we might be able to help predict\nwhat happens next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135954,"text":"Let's consult a graph."},{"time":140622,"text":"Since the invention of scuba,"},{"time":142027,"text":"scientists have measured\nthe amount of coral on the seafloor,"},{"time":145032,"text":"and how it's changed through time."},{"time":147396,"text":"And after centuries\nof ratcheting human pressure,"},{"time":149881,"text":"Caribbean reefs met one of three fates."},{"time":152954,"text":"Some reefs lost their corals very quickly."},{"time":157245,"text":"Some reefs lost their corals more slowly,"},{"time":160713,"text":"but kind of ended up in the same place."},{"time":163730,"text":"OK, so far this is not going very well."},{"time":166244,"text":"But some reefs in the Caribbean --"},{"time":168531,"text":"the ones best protected"},{"time":170448,"text":"and the ones a little\nfurther from humans --"},{"time":173186,"text":"they managed to hold onto their corals."},{"time":177407,"text":"Give us a challenge."},{"time":180089,"text":"And, we almost never saw a reef hit zero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184290,"text":"The second time I cried underwater"},{"time":186800,"text":"was on the north shore of Curaçao, 2011."},{"time":190234,"text":"It was the calmest day of the year,"},{"time":191942,"text":"but it's always pretty\nsketchy diving there."},{"time":194335,"text":"My boyfriend and I swam against the waves."},{"time":196455,"text":"I watched my compass\nso we could find our way back out,"},{"time":199153,"text":"and he watched for sharks,"},{"time":200807,"text":"and after 20 minutes of swimming\nthat felt like an hour,"},{"time":203687,"text":"we finally dropped down to the reef,"},{"time":205427,"text":"and I was so shocked,"},{"time":207010,"text":"and I was so happy"},{"time":208680,"text":"that my eyes filled with tears."},{"time":211399,"text":"There were corals 1,000 years old\nlined up one after another."},{"time":217176,"text":"They had survived the entire history\nof European colonialism in the Caribbean,"},{"time":221886,"text":"and for centuries before that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225645,"text":"I never knew what a coral could do\nwhen it was given a chance to thrive."},{"time":230840,"text":"The truth is that even\nas we lose so many corals,"},{"time":234247,"text":"even as we go through\nthis massive coral die-off,"},{"time":237327,"text":"some reefs will survive."},{"time":239912,"text":"Some will be ragged on the edge,"},{"time":241590,"text":"some will be beautiful."},{"time":244091,"text":"And by protecting shorelines\nand giving us food to eat"},{"time":246806,"text":"and supporting tourism,"},{"time":248579,"text":"they will still be worth\nbillions and billions of dollars a year."},{"time":252223,"text":"The best time to protect a reef\nwas 50 years ago,"},{"time":254838,"text":"but the second-best time is right now."},{"time":259295,"text":"Even as we go through bleaching events,"},{"time":261270,"text":"more frequent and in more places,"},{"time":263837,"text":"some corals will be able to recover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266972,"text":"We had a bleaching event\nin 2010 in the Caribbean"},{"time":269848,"text":"that took off big patches of skin\non boulder corals like these."},{"time":274352,"text":"This coral lost half of its skin."},{"time":276989,"text":"But if you look at the side\nof this coral a few years later,"},{"time":281240,"text":"this coral is actually healthy again."},{"time":283612,"text":"It's doing what a healthy coral does."},{"time":285933,"text":"It's making copies of its polyps,"},{"time":288055,"text":"it's fighting back the algae"},{"time":289534,"text":"and it's reclaiming its territory."},{"time":292375,"text":"If a few polyps survive,"},{"time":293564,"text":"a coral can regrow;"},{"time":294761,"text":"it just needs time and protection\nand a reasonable temperature."},{"time":299368,"text":"Some corals can regrow in 10 years --"},{"time":301201,"text":"others take a lot longer."},{"time":302948,"text":"But the more stresses\nwe take off them locally --"},{"time":305623,"text":"things like overfishing,\nsewage pollution, fertilizer pollution,"},{"time":309641,"text":"dredging, coastal construction --"},{"time":312110,"text":"the better they can hang on\nas we stabilize the climate,"},{"time":315004,"text":"and the faster they can regrow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317946,"text":"And as we go through the long,\ntough and necessary process"},{"time":321708,"text":"of stabilizing the climate\nof planet Earth,"},{"time":324337,"text":"some new corals will still be born."},{"time":327323,"text":"This is what I study in my research."},{"time":329678,"text":"We try to understand\nhow corals make babies,"},{"time":332249,"text":"and how those babies\nfind their way to the reef,"},{"time":334947,"text":"and we invent new methods\nto help them survive"},{"time":337273,"text":"those early, fragile life stages."},{"time":340084,"text":"One of my favorite\ncoral babies of all time"},{"time":343109,"text":"showed up right after Hurricane Omar."},{"time":345143,"text":"It's the same species\nI was studying before the storm,"},{"time":347858,"text":"but you almost never see\nbabies of this species --"},{"time":350314,"text":"it's really rare."},{"time":351553,"text":"This is actually an endangered species."},{"time":354399,"text":"In this photo, this little baby coral,\nthis little circle of polyps,"},{"time":357919,"text":"is a few years old."},{"time":359796,"text":"Like its cousins that bleach,"},{"time":361289,"text":"it's fighting back the algae."},{"time":363149,"text":"And like its cousins on the north shore,"},{"time":365098,"text":"it's aiming to live for 1,000 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369198,"text":"What's happening in the world\nand in the ocean"},{"time":372072,"text":"has changed our time horizon."},{"time":374637,"text":"We can be incredibly pessimistic\non the short term,"},{"time":377700,"text":"and mourn what we lost"},{"time":379039,"text":"and what we really took for granted."},{"time":382208,"text":"But we can still be optimistic\non the long term,"},{"time":384982,"text":"and we can still be ambitious\nabout what we fight for"},{"time":387484,"text":"and what we expect from our governments,"},{"time":390606,"text":"from our planet."},{"time":392544,"text":"Corals have been living on planet Earth\nfor hundreds of millions of years."},{"time":396298,"text":"They survived the extinction\nof the dinosaurs."},{"time":398515,"text":"They're badasses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400369,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401870,"text":"An individual coral can go through\ntremendous trauma and fully recover"},{"time":406433,"text":"if it's given a chance\nand it's given protection."},{"time":410222,"text":"Corals have always\nbeen playing the long game,"},{"time":413719,"text":"and now so are we."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415792,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416969,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}